  "prompt": "How do you invert your selection in Photoshop?",
  "response": "Inverting your selection in Photoshop is a useful technique when you want to affect everything outside of your current selection rather than the selection itself. Here are the steps to invert your selection:\n\n1. **Make a Selection**: First, use any of the selection tools like the Marquee Tool, Lasso Tool, or Quick Selection Tool to create your initial selection on the image.\n\n2. **Invert the Selection**:\n   - Go to the menu bar and click on **\"Select\"**.\n   - From the dropdown menu, choose **\"Inverse\"**.\n   - Alternatively, you can use the keyboard shortcut **Shift + Ctrl + I** (Windows) or **Shift + Command + I** (Mac) to quickly invert the selection.\n\nAfter inverting the selection, any adjustments you apply will affect everything outside of your initial selection. This can be useful for various photo editing tasks such as applying filters, adjustments, or masks to the non-selected areas of your image.",
